cd squid-6.10/

INSTALL, QUICKSTART
---------------------

To build and install the Squid Cache, type:

        % ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/squid
        % make all
        % make install

To run a Cache, you will need to:

        1. customize the squid.conf configuration file:
              % vi /usr/local/squid/etc/squid.conf

        2. Initialise the cache:
              % /usr/local/squid/sbin/squid -z

        3. start the cache:
              % /usr/local/squid/sbin/squid
----------------

./configure --prefix=/usr/local/squid

make all

컴파일 시간 많이 걸림

make install

du -h /usr/local/squid/
...
110M

vi /usr/local/squid/etc/squid.conf
...
# should be allowed
acl localnet src 150.183.234.0/24
acl localnet src 150.183.249.0/24
acl localnet src 150.183.250.0/24
...

# Squid normally listens to port 3128
http_port 3128
...
# Uncomment and adjust the following to add a disk cache directory.
cache_dir ufs /usr/local/squid/var/cache/squid 100 16 256
...
cache_effective_user   squid



adduser squid

chown -R squid.squid /usr/local/squid/var

도움말
/usr/local/squid/sbin/squid  -h

디렉터리 초기화 하기
/usr/local/squid/sbin/squid -z
   -z        Create missing swap directories and then exit.

시작하기
/usr/local/squid/sbin/squid  

ps ax | grep squid

netstat -antp  | grep squid




